## Windsurf / Cascade-specific notes

Three rules matter most when working in this repo via Windsurf:

1. **`just verify --quick` is the definition of "done".** Do not declare a
   task complete until it exits 0. `--quick` runs the fast slice (lint,
   typecheck, format, smoke) — the right pre-claim gate.

2. **Findings are clickable in the Problems panel.** `.vscode/tasks.json`
   ships problem matchers for Ruff, Pyright, tsc, Biome. Run the `verify`
   task (`Ctrl+Shift+B`); click any entry to jump to the line.

3. **Never write bare relative paths from harness code.** `Path(".verify/...")`
   is wrong — thread `cwd` explicitly so the harness works regardless of
   invocation directory. See AGENTS.md §Tool conventions.

